title: Microsoft SQL Architect for Enterprise Software Provider - Full time/long term
description:
Microsoft SQL Architect
US – Cleveland, Sarasota, Remote

OVERVIEW 
Pulse is looking for a talented Microsoft SQL Architect to join our team. The ideal candidate would possess a diverse technical skillset including experience in application development in Microsoft .NET, database design and administration in SQL Server. A passion for automation and process improvement is a valued characteristic. Experience in operations and production support is also critical. 

As a SQL Architect at Pulse, you will be responsible for the performance, integrity and security of the database. You will also be involved in the planning and development of the database, as well as troubleshooting any issues on behalf of the users. You will have the opportunity to work with a constantly growing team on an enterprise application used by some of the largest manufacturers and retailers and health organization in the world. 
 

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES AND ACCOUNTABILITIES 
•	Considering both back-end organization of data and front-end accessibility and performance for end-users
•	Building and maintaining a Data for our largest clients
•	Refining the logical design so that it can be translated into a specific data model
•	Further refining the physical design to meet system storage requirements
•	Building and enhancing the functionality of our Microsoft-based application suite
•	Helping establish and maintain data security, recovery and operational procedures
•	Helping automate and improve development workflow 
•	Writing and maintaining database documentation, including data and technical standards, procedures and definitions for the data dictionary (metadata)
•	Communicating regularly with technical, applications and operational staff to ensure database integrity and security
•	Installing new applications and customizing existing applications in order to make them fit for purpose
 

QUALIFICATIONS
•	Degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or Information Technology is preferred
•	Experience documenting a database environment (and using tools to facilitate this)
•	Experience keeping a development and production environment in sync 
•	2 to 4 years of Microsoft .NET development experience
•	4 to 6 years of SQL Server Architect experience
•	1 to 2 years’ experience in mobile application development 
•	2 to 4 years’ experience supporting production applications 
•	Familiarity with the principles of database design 
•	Familiarity with application development patterns and practices 
•	Good communication, organizational and teamwork skills 
•	Problem-solving and good analytical skills 
•	Flexibility and adaptability
•	Ability to work to tight deadlines under pressure 
•	Business awareness and understanding of business requirements of IT
•	Willingness to keep up to date with developments in new technology
